++ <dos>
[[# dos]]DOS and optics plots require integrals of the kind 
[[math label]] 

											g(\omega_i)=\frac{\Omega}{(2\pi)^3}\int_{\rm BZ}
											f({ \bf k}) \delta(\omega_i-e({\bf k}))d{ \bf k}.
										
[[/math]]
These are calculated by first interpolating the functions [[$ e({ \bf k}) $]]and [[$ f({ \bf k}) $]]with the trilinear method on a much finer mesh whose size is determined by {{ ngrdos }}. Then the [[$ \omega $]]-dependent histogram of the integrand is accumulated over the fine mesh. If the output function is noisy then either {{ ngrdos }}should be increased or {{ nwdos }}decreased. Alternatively, the output function can be artificially smoothed up to a level given by {{ nsmdos }}. This is the number of successive 3-point averages to be applied to the function [[$ g $]].
++++* Attributes:
+++++* @sqados

[[# sqados]]spin-quantisation axis in Cartesian coordinates used when plotting the spin-resolved DOS (z-axis by default)

**type:** vect3d **default-value:** 0.0  0.0  1.0 
+++++* @lmirep

[[# lmirep]]When lmirep is set to .true., the spherical harmonic basis is transformed into one in which the site symmetries are block diagonal. Band characters determined from the density ma- trix expressed in this basis correspond to irreducible representations, and allow the partial DOS to be resolved into physically relevant contributions, for example eg and t2g .

**type:** xs:boolean **default-value:** false 
+++++* @nwdos

[[# nwdos]]number of frequency/energy points in the DOS or op- integer 500 tics plot

**type:** xs:integer **default-value:** 500 
+++++* @ngrdos

[[# ngrdos]]effective k-point mesh size to be used for Brillouin zone integer

**type:** xs:integer **default-value:** 100 
+++++* @scissor
 [[#scissor see]] 
+++++* @nsmdos

[[# nsmdos]]level of smoothing applied to DOS/optics output integer 0

**type:** xs:integer **default-value:** 0 
+++++* @winddos

[[# winddos]]frequency/energy window for the DOS or optics plot

**type:** vect2d **default-value:** .5 .5 

